  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Relief and Assistance to Conflict Affected Populations in Marib, Al Hudaydah, and Taizz Governorates, Yemen</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this action, IOM is providing coordination, information management and emergency relief services, including cash and voucher assistance (CVA), that supports vulnerable populations and humanitarian actors in Yemen. This project is advancing humanitarian response in Marib and the west coast region (Hudaydah and southern Taizz) where urgent interventions are required to meet the needs of acutely displaced populations. More specifically, IOM is providing shelter and non-food items, and water, sanitation and hygiene (WASH), CVA and camp coordination and camp management support to internally displaced persons (IDPs) in 43 IOM-supported IDP sites (34 in Marib, and 9 in Al Hudaydah). WASH services will also be extended to underserved IDP sites in southern Taizz.</narrative>
  </description>
